title: 304 - Stray Dogs
description:
"Entrepreneurship is filling the void in the marketplace that the marketplace is calling for consciously or subconsciously. Entrepreneurs look and listen to what is happening in the marketplace and they respond. They also look and listen to what's not happening in the marketplace and they respond as well."
These are the words and entrepreneurial philosophy of entrepreneur, radio host, speaker, and owner of The Breakfast Klub, Marcus Davis. Marcus is the epitome of what African-American entrepreneurship can and should look like. Marcus candidly shares his journey toward 20 years of sustained business. Marcus had a vision of being an example of what African-American restaurants can do in the marketplace and he is killing the game. Listen intently, take notes, and be inspired to take your entrepreneurial goals to the next level.
Listener Perks

ORGANIFI is giving our listeners up to 20% off of their order! Just go to www.organifi.com/success. Their superfood green juice powder allows you to get your greens anytime, anywhere while on the go.


SHIPSTATION allows online sellers to get your products to your customers as easy as possible. Go to www.shipstation.com and use PROMO code SUCCESS.


BLOCKFI bitcoin reward credit card lets you earn an unlimited 1.5% in bitcoin on all qualified purchases. Making everyday purchases puts bitcoin in your pocket. Apply now for a $25 bonus in crypto at www.blockfi.com/success
